{{Refimprove|date=October 2010}}
'''The Doorpost Film Project''' is one of the largest annual, [[online]] [[film festivals]] in the world, established by Jason Atkins with Project Director Nathan Elliott, Project Coordinator Brian Jerin, Supervising Producer Jonathan Shepard, Web developer Dana Luther, Editor Gabe Cox and Designer Will Hill.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.filmthreat.com/interviews/1203 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-10-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101023070834/http://www.filmthreat.com/interviews/1203/ |archivedate=2010-10-23 |df= }}</ref> It has 3 stages that take place from October through November of the following year.
==Winners== 2008 Winner was John Gray with his film "Before I Wake". *The 2009 Festival Champion was [[Butterfly Circus]] directed by [[Joshua Weigel]].
==Prizes== The 2010 Short Film Contest sponsored by the Doorpost Film Project is awarding over $160,000 in prizes.<ref>http://www.thedoorpost.com</ref>
==Mission== The Doorpost Film Project aims to inspire and reward aspiring and beginning filmmakers to make quality films.<ref>http://www.studiodaily.com/main/.../Doorpost-Film-Contest-Opens-Doors-for-Independent-Filmmakers-Awards-Exceed-$300000_9095.html</ref>
==Dissolution== The Doorpost Film Project is dissolved. In accordance with Tennessee Code Title 48 for Nonprofit Corporations Chapter 64 Part 1 § 48-64-104 The Doorpost Foundation has been dissolved as of 11:59pm June 30, 2013. http://www.thedoorpost.com/
