==Name==
The word ”kurultaj” and its variations in the [[Turkic languages]] translates as “meeting of the tribes”. It occurs amongst tribal nations and practically in all the nomadic cultures. Hungarian nomadic tribes also held these meetings, a fact that is mentioned in Byzantine and Arab written sources. At such meetings, important decisions were made, in particular, the leaders of the tribes would meet often to discuss military decisions and strategies.<ref>Official website of Kurultáj - [http://kurultaj.hu/english/ "Information: History of Kurultaj"]</ref>

==Events==
The Kurultaj of 2013 took place from 9 to 11 August.<ref>[https://www.kyivpost.com/multimedia/photo/the-kurultaj-festival-takes-place-in-hungary-328266.html ''Kurultaj Festival delves into Hungarian history''] in ''[[Kyiv Post]]'' on August 12, 2013</ref>

The Kurultaj of 2014 took place at [[Bugac]] in the [[Southern Great Plain]] region in [[Hungary]].<ref>[http://dailynewshungary.com/kurultaj-nomadic-culture-and-tribal-traditions-photo-gallery/ ''KURULTAJ – Nomadic Culture and Tribal Traditions''] in ''Daily News Hungary'' on August 14, 2014</ref>

The events of 2015 were organized by the [[Hungarian Turan Foundation]] with contributions from the [[Turkish Cooperation and Coordination Agency]] (TİKA) and named the year's event Ancestors Day. Representatives from the governments of Hungary and [[Turkey]] joined the festivities as well.<ref>[http://www.dailysabah.com/history/2015/08/18/turkey-hungary-jointly-commemorate-atilla-the-hun Turkey, Hungary jointly commemorate Atilla the Hun]</ref>

The Kurultáj of 2016 took place from 12 to 14 August at Bugac.<ref>[http://kurultaj.hu/2016/01/a-2016-evi-kurultaj-idopontja-augusztus-12-13-14/ Official site]</ref>

