{{about|the international music festivals held throughout the United States|the annual three-day multicultural event held in Edmonton|Edmonton Heritage Festival}}
{{Multiple issues|
{{refimprove|date=April 2013}}
{{primary sources|date=April 2013}}
}}

'''Heritage Festival''' refers to one of about 100 [[music]] [[festival]]s held throughout the [[United States]] where [[middle school]] and [[high school]]-aged musical ensembles are adjudicated on a national standard.  These groups include [[choir]]s, [[Musical ensemble|bands]], and [[orchestra]]s.  The festivals were founded in 1980, and are currently a part of [[WorldStrides]] OnStage Programs. The top performing groups in these Heritage Festivals are invited to perform in the Festival of Gold Elite Festival Series or the Festival at [[Carnegie Hall]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldstridesheritageperformance.org/fog/festival_of_gold.php|title=Festival of Gold|work=WorldStrides Heritage Performance|accessdate=2013-04-21}}</ref>

