'''''Stepping Out''''' was a British [[competitive dancing]] [[talent show]] that aired on [[ITV (TV channel)|ITV]] from 31 August to 28 September 2013 and was hosted by [[Davina McCall]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Drewett |first=Meg |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a507201/davina-mccall-to-host-itv-strictly-rival-lineup-revealed.html |title=Davina McCall to host ITV 'Strictly' rival: Lineup revealed|publisher=Digital Spy|date=2013-08-16|accessdate=2013-08-17}}</ref> The judging panel, referred to on the show as "the front row", was confirmed on 29 August 2013 and consists of [[Mel B]], [[Jason Gardiner]] and [[Wayne Sleep]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.itv.com/steppingout/news/steppingoutfrontrowrevealed/ |title=Front Row panel revealed - Stepping Out|publisher=[[itv.com]]|date=2013-08-21|accessdate=2013-09-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.itv.com/steppingout/frontrow/ |title=Front Row - Stepping Out|publisher=ITV|accessdate=2013-09-14}}</ref> Unlike other similar dance shows, the dancers were all couples in real life, not one celebrity plus one professional dancer.

